So, it's a real quantity.

00:19:37.320 --> 00:19:41.820
And it's called a
probability current.

00:19:41.820 --> 00:19:47.520
And it goes together with
this probability density,

00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:56.480
this probability density
that we wrote over here.

00:19:56.480 --> 00:20:00.260
So it's the current
associated to that density.

00:20:06.870 --> 00:20:09.480
Let's think a second
what this means.

00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:14.180
In electromagnetism, you have
currents and charged densities.

00:20:14.180 --> 00:20:19.580
So in E&amp;M, you have a current.

00:20:19.580 --> 00:20:22.790
It's a vector and
a charged density.

00:20:22.790 --> 00:20:25.500
Now, this current
could also be a vector.

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:27.870
If you're working in
more than one dimension,

00:20:27.870 --> 00:20:29.790
it would be a vector.

00:20:29.790 --> 00:20:31.730
But if you have
electromagnetism,

00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:36.040
the most famous thing associated
to electromagnetism currents

00:20:36.040 --> 00:20:39.800
and charged densities is the
so-called conservation law.

00:20:44.860 --> 00:20:47.490
This differential
equations satisfied

00:20:47.490 --> 00:20:49.950
by the current and the density.

00:20:49.950 --> 00:20:54.770
Divergence of j plus d
Rho dt is equal to zero.

00:20:54.770 --> 00:20:56.983
That means charge conservation.

00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:01.550
You may or may
